GUARANTY TRUST COMPANY, Plaintiff in Error, v. G. F. GROHE-HENRICH & COMPANY, Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 10, 1928. No. 20. Davis, Polk, Wardwell, Gardiner & Eeed, of New York City (William C. Cannon, Theodore Kiendl, and Eussel S. Coutant, all of New York City, of counsel), for plaintiff in error. Kellogg, Emory, Inness-Brown & Cuthell, of New York City, for defendant in error.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PEE CURIAM.

Eeversed in open court on confession of error.
